<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Drag" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Drag,</orth> to pull, to draw, to trail: <cit><quote>my affairs d. me homeward,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what impediments d. back our expedition,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 3, 19</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll d. thee up and down,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.51" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 51</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.229" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 229</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.10.86" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 10, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 129</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 1, 35</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>